Owen: That's the same song
they played yesterday.

01:01.044 --> 01:02.277
That's weird.

01:02.312 --> 01:03.953
- [ Door closes ]
- Cat: [ Groans ]

01:03.988 --> 01:07.056
Night shift. Brutal.

01:07.091 --> 01:09.058
Good night.

01:15.599 --> 01:16.732
Blake:
Hey, O!

01:16.767 --> 01:17.867
Owen:
Wait a second.

01:17.902 --> 01:19.102
This all happened yesterday.

01:19.136 --> 01:21.137
Am I stuck
in some sort of time loop?

01:21.172 --> 01:22.172
Blake, watch out!

01:22.206 --> 01:24.007
Blake:
Whoa!

01:24.041 --> 01:26.009
Whoa. Thank you.

01:26.043 --> 01:28.945
Owen: I think I'm trapped
in some sort of a time loop.

01:28.979 --> 01:30.446
Blake:
Yeah, okay, cool.

01:30.480 --> 01:33.116
Owen: I can practice this day
as much as I want.

01:33.150 --> 01:34.717
Blake:
Yeah, all right.

01:34.751 --> 01:36.829
- Owen: Yeah!
- Blake: Yeah.

01:38.655 --> 01:40.089
Whoa-ho!

01:40.124 --> 01:42.767
Not gonna make the same mistake
I did yesterday,

01:42.806 --> 01:44.144
smashing through a plate of glass

01:44.295 --> 01:48.007
like some 21st century's answer
to Charlie Chaplin.

01:48.833 --> 01:49.799
Whoa!

01:49.867 --> 01:50.900
Aah!

01:50.968 --> 01:52.501
Oh, my God!

01:52.536 --> 01:56.639
I'm pretty sure my bone
is sticking out of my [bleep] leg!

01:56.673 --> 01:58.516
Oh, my God, I'm so scared!

01:59.210 --> 02:00.509
Glenn:
Hey, Owen!

02:00.544 --> 02:03.713
Do you have any special skills
or talents you want to perform

02:03.747 --> 02:05.248
for the troops in today's show?

02:05.282 --> 02:07.116
Owen: I wish I could play
the trumpet.

02:07.184 --> 02:09.085
Glenn: Great!
Your wish is my command.

02:09.119 --> 02:09.853
[ Chuckles ]

02:09.919 --> 02:11.754
I didn't know he could play
the trumpet.

02:11.788 --> 02:12.755
That's great.

02:12.823 --> 02:15.124
Owen: Guess I better learn
to play the trumpet.

02:15.192 --> 02:17.560
Good thing I have an eternity
to practice.

02:17.594 --> 02:18.228
Sy:
Glenn!

02:18.295 --> 02:20.063
Do not make me sorry

02:20.130 --> 02:22.198
that I put you in charge
of booking this show.

02:22.233 --> 02:23.603
Where are the celebrities?

02:23.641 --> 02:24.950
Glenn:
Planes running a little late, Sy.

02:25.102 --> 02:26.327
- They will make it.
- Sy: Who's coming?

02:26.470 --> 02:28.022
Glenn: [ Scoffs ]
I want it to be a surprise.

02:28.139 --> 02:29.504
Sy:
No, you don't.

02:29.639 --> 02:30.954
Bono's hologram?

02:31.077 --> 02:33.076
Glenn: Well, you know,
it was just a little bit more difficult

02:33.110 --> 02:34.543
to book Bono
than I anticipated.

02:34.578 --> 02:36.012
Sy: Glenn Close?
Who is he?

02:36.046 --> 02:37.080
Glenn:
All the good celebrities

02:37.114 --> 02:40.549
are doing this MTV-sponsored show
for the troops in Dubai.

02:40.584 --> 02:41.918
Sy:
You better work it out,

02:41.986 --> 02:44.287
or I'm canceling
the staff pizza party on Sunday.

02:44.355 --> 02:46.789
Glenn: No pizza?
You monster.

02:46.823 --> 02:47.723
Sy:
Wait a minute.

02:47.758 --> 02:49.325
- Owen plays the trumpet?
- Glenn: Yeah.

02:49.360 --> 02:50.960
- Sy: Can't wait.
- Glenn: I know!

02:50.995 --> 02:53.096
- Sy: Who knew?
- Glenn: It should be good, right?

02:53.130 --> 02:55.531
I think I might bump Owen up
and then pop to Bono's hologram,

02:55.565 --> 02:57.577
then end big
with this Glenn Close guy.

02:59.870 --> 03:01.296
Chief:
[ Sighs ]

03:03.040 --> 03:04.974
Everyone, I have a message.

03:05.009 --> 03:08.811
The plane containing
our celebrity holograms

03:08.845 --> 03:11.596
has been shot down
over the sea of Japan.

03:12.649 --> 03:14.984
There were very few survivors.

03:15.019 --> 03:17.620
Glenn: Did any of the holograms
make it?

03:17.654 --> 03:18.288
Bono?

03:18.322 --> 03:19.722
Chief:
The hard drive

03:19.756 --> 03:23.192
containing Bono's hologram
crashed.

03:23.227 --> 03:24.294
Literally.

03:24.328 --> 03:26.930
Dori:
Such young technology.

03:26.997 --> 03:27.997
Glenn:
That's it.

03:28.032 --> 03:30.233
There's no stars
and stripes show today.

03:30.301 --> 03:31.842
I failed.

03:31.877 --> 03:34.203
Owen: Don't worry. You still
got me for the big show tonight.

03:34.238 --> 03:37.773
I'm off to my first trumpet lesson ever
right now.

03:37.808 --> 03:38.975
Glenn:
Oh.

03:39.043 --> 03:40.977
Chief:
Oh, Glenn, uh,

03:41.045 --> 03:44.981
since you're letting Owen learn
the trumpet on the day of the show,

03:45.049 --> 03:47.250
how about you let me
sing a song?

03:47.284 --> 03:48.929
Glenn:
No offense, Chief,

03:49.011 --> 03:50.726
but I'm sure
you're a terrible singer,

03:50.761 --> 03:54.723
and people don't like
to look at you at all.

03:54.758 --> 03:55.992
You know what I mean?

03:56.026 --> 03:57.293
Dori, look at Chief.

03:57.328 --> 03:58.361
Dori:
I'd rather not.

03:58.395 --> 04:00.196
Glenn: See?
She cannot do it.

04:00.230 --> 04:02.231
Sal: Attention staff...
Incoming wounded.

04:02.266 --> 04:05.105
Survivors from Glenn's failure due
in two minutes.

04:06.437 --> 04:09.138
Chet: These are the lucky ones
who survived the crash.

04:09.173 --> 04:10.739
The unlucky ones?

04:10.774 --> 04:11.874
Not as lucky.

04:11.908 --> 04:14.877
Sy: Hey! It's international pop star
Chase McKeever!

04:14.945 --> 04:16.745
Yo, yo, bro, call me C-Werd.

04:16.779 --> 04:19.182
Chet: Everyone!
It's official!

04:19.216 --> 04:21.017
This is happening!

04:21.051 --> 04:23.353
I've got McKeever fever!

04:23.387 --> 04:24.720
I'm gonna faint.

04:24.788 --> 04:25.888
Someone catch me!

04:25.922 --> 04:29.725
Sy: You were going to surprise me
with Chase McKeever?

04:29.759 --> 04:32.095
I am so pleased, Glenn.

04:32.129 --> 04:33.096
[ Smooches ]

04:33.163 --> 04:34.130
Everybody listen.

04:34.164 --> 04:36.699
I'm Dr. Marnie Weiss,
Chase's personal physician.

04:36.733 --> 04:39.735
I tour with Chase so I can take care
of any nodules and lumps.

04:39.769 --> 04:40.836
Sy:
On his voice box?

04:40.871 --> 04:42.872
Yes, on his voice box.
Let's say that.

04:42.906 --> 04:45.408
I'm also his swagger coach.

04:45.442 --> 04:48.777
Sy: Dr. Weiss, you take care of Chase
and make him brand-new,

04:48.845 --> 04:50.946
as long as he's ready
for the show today.

04:51.015 --> 04:53.316
We are not doing your concert.
[ Scoffs ]

04:53.384 --> 04:55.192
We're on the first flight to Dubai

04:55.233 --> 04:58.321
to do the "MTV Salutes the Troops"
concert.

04:58.355 --> 05:00.323
Let's go, C-Werd.

05:03.360 --> 05:06.296
Sy: Why can't you be more
like MTV?

05:08.165 --> 05:10.307
Glenn: Now I know
how VH1 feels.

05:10.701 --> 05:14.904
[ Trumpet plays off-key ]

05:14.938 --> 05:16.005
Owen:
[ Gasps ]

05:16.040 --> 05:17.340
This is so hard.

05:17.374 --> 05:19.808
The trumpet
is a challenging instrument.

05:19.843 --> 05:22.178
It takes years
to become proficient.

05:22.212 --> 05:23.413
Owen:
That's okay.

05:23.480 --> 05:25.381
I'm in a time loop.

05:25.416 --> 05:27.638
Ah. I got it.

05:27.885 --> 05:29.385
Sal:
Attention staff.

05:29.420 --> 05:31.421
Never mind.
You're not worth it.

05:31.488 --> 05:32.121
That is all.

05:32.156 --> 05:34.090
Ooh! FroYo, yo!

05:34.124 --> 05:35.925
Yeah.

05:35.959 --> 05:36.992
Aw, damn.

05:37.027 --> 05:40.096
I got FroYo all over my Yo-Yo,
yo.

05:40.130 --> 05:41.497
Sy:
Nurse Dori,

05:41.532 --> 05:43.933
would you please remove Chet
from the Celebrity Room?

05:43.967 --> 05:44.833
Doesn't matter.

05:44.868 --> 05:46.469
Our plane to Dubai
leaves in 30 minutes.

05:46.503 --> 05:48.071
Chet:
I have McKeever fever!

05:48.105 --> 05:50.139
Glenn: Did someone say
McKeever fever?

05:50.174 --> 05:51.340
[ Sighs ]
This guy again.

05:51.375 --> 05:53.476
Yes, he has McKeever fever.

05:53.544 --> 05:55.945
Glenn: McKeever fever
is a very rare, serious virus

05:55.979 --> 05:58.481
isolated at the McKeever Medical
Conference in 1909.

05:58.515 --> 06:00.116
Chet:
Yeah, you see?

06:00.150 --> 06:02.708
Glenn: Dori, quick...
Give me 40 cc of epinephrine

06:02.779 --> 06:05.029
and prep a tetranizanol drip,
stat!

06:07.924 --> 06:09.225
Chet:
[ Groans ]

06:09.259 --> 06:10.893
Glenn:
The worst of it is over.

06:10.927 --> 06:12.128
Chet:
Thank you, Dr. Richie.

06:12.162 --> 06:13.762
Glenn:
Of course.

06:13.797 --> 06:14.930
It's okay.

06:14.965 --> 06:16.199
It happens.

06:16.233 --> 06:18.033
You don't have to say anything.

06:18.068 --> 06:20.035
What do you expect me to say?

06:20.070 --> 06:21.237
I'm sorry?

06:21.271 --> 06:23.306
I guess I'm the bad guy here.

06:23.340 --> 06:24.173
Come on, Chase.

06:24.208 --> 06:25.808
Get your do-rag.
We're leaving.

06:25.842 --> 06:27.310
Sy:
Could I...

06:27.344 --> 06:28.478
Wait, wait.

06:28.545 --> 06:29.979
Glenn, make this right.

06:30.013 --> 06:32.348
The concert is in one hour.

06:32.382 --> 06:33.817
Glenn:
Pizza party.

06:34.184 --> 06:35.712
Pizza party.

06:36.453 --> 06:40.223
[ Indistinct conversations ]

06:40.257 --> 06:44.494
Okay! Well, first up...
You know her.

06:44.561 --> 06:47.130
You've probably avoided
staring at her around the base.

06:47.164 --> 06:49.064
Ladies and gentlemen,
it's Chief!

06:49.133 --> 06:50.299
Chief:
Ha! Oh, my God!

06:50.334 --> 06:51.786
Cat:
Go, Chief.

06:55.272 --> 07:02.445
Chief: [ Deep voice ]
♪ I am a poor wayfaring stranger ♪

07:02.479 --> 07:04.147
♪ travelling through... ♪

07:04.181 --> 07:06.282
Glenn: Owen!
Owen, are you ready?

07:06.316 --> 07:08.117
Owen: No, I can't play
this thing yet.

07:08.152 --> 07:09.252
But in a few more months
of todays,

07:09.286 --> 07:11.086
I'll be ready
for today's big show.

07:11.121 --> 07:12.522
Glenn:
You're not in a time loop.

07:12.556 --> 07:14.023
And I can tell by your reaction

07:14.090 --> 07:16.859
that nobody said that to you
until now.

07:16.893 --> 07:18.327
- Owen: Oh.
- Glenn: Yeah.

07:18.362 --> 07:20.329
Owen:
Well, cross me off the list.

07:20.364 --> 07:21.464
Glenn:
Yep, okay.

07:21.498 --> 07:23.599
Chief:
♪ I'm going home ♪

07:23.634 --> 07:25.434
[ Cheers and applause ]

07:25.469 --> 07:26.902
Sy:
Chase!

07:26.936 --> 07:29.138
You... you convinced Chase
to stay?

07:29.173 --> 07:30.540
Glenn:
I didn't do anything.

07:30.574 --> 07:31.974
Yes, you did.

07:32.008 --> 07:35.187
You saved two lives today...
Chet's and mine,

07:35.260 --> 07:37.413
by teaching me
a lesson about humility.

07:37.447 --> 07:39.511
Yeah.
Let's make some panties drop, yo!

07:41.017 --> 07:42.418
What's up?!
It's the C-Werd!

07:42.452 --> 07:43.919
[ Cheers and applause ]

07:43.987 --> 07:44.953
[ Rock music plays ]

07:44.988 --> 07:47.490
♪ You make my heart go ♪

07:47.524 --> 07:48.357
♪ up and down ♪

07:48.392 --> 07:50.359
Glenn:
Oh, thank you so much.

07:50.394 --> 07:53.196
Thank me after you meet
international pop superstar

07:53.230 --> 07:54.029
Madonna!

07:54.064 --> 07:54.997
Glenn:
What?!

07:55.031 --> 07:56.131
[ Cheers and applause ]

07:56.200 --> 07:57.132
Cat:
Oh, my God.

07:57.167 --> 07:59.131
It's really Madonna.

08:01.004 --> 08:05.007
[ Deep voice ]
♪ Let's keep this party growin' ♪

08:05.041 --> 08:07.042
Please welcome Rihanna!

08:07.077 --> 08:09.545
[ Cheers and applause ]

08:09.580 --> 08:11.080
Sy:
Rihanna, too?!

08:11.147 --> 08:13.048
♪ Touch me everywhere, man ♪

08:13.083 --> 08:14.650
♪ touch me everywhere ♪

08:14.685 --> 08:16.319
Louis C.K.!

08:16.353 --> 08:18.087
[ Cheers and applause ]

08:18.121 --> 08:19.522
Glenn:
Oh, Louis!

08:19.556 --> 08:21.190
Yeah, hi.

08:21.225 --> 08:23.392
I guess I'm here so...

08:23.427 --> 08:25.394
I'm standing next to Rihanna,

08:25.429 --> 08:28.297
which is... I've never felt
fatter and whiter.

08:28.332 --> 08:29.932
Cat: Oh, my God.
He gets me.

08:30.166 --> 08:31.234
He gets me.

08:31.268 --> 08:33.869
Freddie Mercury!

08:33.937 --> 08:34.903
Ha!

08:34.938 --> 08:37.607
♪ When I'm all alone ♪

08:37.640 --> 08:39.041
Glenn:
He looks great!

08:39.075 --> 08:41.443
I just want Kleenex and cake.

08:41.477 --> 08:42.477
That's all I want.

08:42.511 --> 08:46.181
And international swimsuit
supermodel Kate Upton!

08:46.216 --> 08:49.151
[ Cheers and applause ]

08:49.219 --> 08:50.431
Glenn:
Br-br-br-br-br-br!

08:52.989 --> 08:54.590
♪ When I'm all alone ♪

08:54.625 --> 08:56.259
♪ Everybody dance ♪

08:56.326 --> 08:57.660
♪ Touch me everywhere ♪

08:57.694 --> 08:59.928
I have a house.
I have this... It's a place.

08:59.996 --> 09:00.663
I have it.

09:00.731 --> 09:02.565
Guys,
stop masturbating at me.

09:02.599 --> 09:03.666
Glenn:
This is good.

09:03.700 --> 09:06.034
I wish Owen was here
to see this.

09:06.069 --> 09:08.103
Hey.

09:08.238 --> 09:10.406
Go find your friend.

09:10.440 --> 09:12.141
Glenn:
Thanks.

09:12.208 --> 09:13.342
There he is.

09:13.377 --> 09:16.011
Owen: I'm never gonna learn
to play the trumpet.

09:16.045 --> 09:17.680
- Sure you will.
- Glenn: That's right.

09:17.714 --> 09:19.014
All you have to do is believe

09:19.048 --> 09:22.351
that you're a great trumpet player
and you will be.

09:22.419 --> 09:23.419
Right now.

09:23.487 --> 09:25.521
Owen:
Okay!

09:25.555 --> 09:28.524
♪ Everybody dance ♪

09:28.592 --> 09:34.096
[ "Reveille" plays ]

09:34.130 --> 09:36.999
Glenn: I knew if you believed
in yourself you could do it!

09:37.033 --> 09:39.078
♪ Touch me everywhere ♪

09:42.205 --> 09:43.406
My daughter is a bitch.

09:43.440 --> 09:44.373
Glenn:
[ Laughing ]

09:44.441 --> 09:47.610
♪ Touch me everywhere ♪

09:47.644 --> 09:51.647
[ Cheers and applause ]

09:51.682 --> 09:53.982
Glenn:
What a show.

09:54.017 --> 09:55.083
Ahh.

09:55.118 --> 09:58.621
I only wonder what might have
happened between you and me.

09:58.689 --> 10:02.558
Who says it's too late?

10:02.592 --> 10:04.393
Sy: Guess who's getting
a pizza party.

10:04.428 --> 10:05.494
[ Feedback ]

10:05.529 --> 10:08.354
Chief: [ Voice breaking ]
Everyone, I have a message.

10:09.333 --> 10:13.409
The plane containing
all of the pizza in Japan

10:14.274 --> 10:16.515
has been shot down.

10:17.674 --> 10:20.107
There are no survivors.

10:21.144 --> 10:24.059
Did any toppings survive,
or...

10:29.519 --> 10:31.153
Oh, my God!

10:31.187 --> 10:32.421
Oh, my [bleep] God!

10:32.456 --> 10:33.989
Stop it!

10:34.057 --> 10:35.358
[Bleep]

10:35.392 --> 10:38.026
I'm supposed to be Louis C.K.

10:38.061 --> 10:41.530
They could have got me,
but they got me instead.

10:41.565 --> 10:45.200
[ "Reveille" continues ]

10:45.235 --> 10:46.469
Sal:
Attention staff...

10:46.503 --> 10:48.409
If you were a Japanese woman
with freckles,

10:48.481 --> 10:50.206
you know you have it
pretty good, right?

10:50.474 --> 10:51.914
That is all.

